text: It confuses me the amount of ppl getting upset/angry, saying it shouldn't have Fast and Furious in the title coz it has nothing to do with Fast and Furious. No, it's technically not a F&F movie, it's not Fast 9.... but it is a spin-off so it is still officially a part of the franchise.....  if it was called Fast and Furious: Hobbs & Shaw, then fair enough, I'd understand ppl being pissed.... but that's why the title is how it is.  The movie is called Hobbs & Shaw. The "Fast and Furious presents" bit (with 'presents' being the important word here) is merely an acknowledgement that no, it's not a part of the main storyline, but it is still a part of the franchise.

text: God damn has this series come a long way. I think about the first Fast and Furious and consider it a show that takes itself fairly realistically. The spectacle was there in the drama of the stories of the main characters, in the high stakes they faced on a personal level. Obviously its supposed to be badass, it is, and those cars are still sick but, the scale and scope and focus shifted so powerfully into, admittedly a still badass, but way over the top, almost comic book levels of ridiculous, explosion of badass action heros. They are now the halmarked by Schwarzenegger levels of cheese and overblown personalities. Not to say that at all negatively either, its a style that is right uo my alley, I adore over the top action flicks. I'm actually pumped for this movie. It looks like its going to be fun to watch from start to finish. I love these actors and these tropes, and i dig that it looks like they are going to be on great display with this movie. Its just fun to consider how this ended up based on the perpesctive of the past and where I ever expected the series to go. Even with things having escalated catastrophe level events, it was just as meaningful if not more so when the big risks and motivations driving the characters are rooted in the reality of hard time, the fear of betrayal, the death of a friend, or just the will to survive the hardships of real life in extra ordinary situations. It turned into something so different from the original that i just have to laugh and I love it Bahahahahahahahaha! Okay, thats enough rambling from this one. Cheers to an exciting release, I will be happy to see this movie.

text: Action films are officially dead. Everything that we love about big action blockbusters have disappeared. Real vehicles, real buildings, real explosions, real smoke, real flames, blood squibs, stunts. All gone.  Now every single so-called action film has CGI vehicles, CGI buildings, CGI explosions, CGI smoke, CGI flames, CGI blood, practically no stunts.   The point of an action movie was to watch epic exciting spectacle. Now it's like watching a video game. Why should I be excited by something that was created entirely on a computer?  I'm done with this franchise.

Brixton arrives and kidnaps Shaw's sister and then we have that running down the building scene, they save her and fight some bad guys on bikes including Brixton. They then go to see a woman, a friend of the Shaw family who gives them weapons and an flight to go to Brixton's secret base and fight a lot of bad guys before they get captured and get tortured by him. They escape of course similar to how they escape in Fate of the furious, fighting bad guys while a cool song plays in the background! We then have that Shaw turning the car 360° and later destroying the base. They then need a hiding place so they go to "Hobbs's Family Island" where they do a ridiculous thing (see trailer) and fight more bad guys while a cool song plays in the background! We then have that heli scene with The Rock doing that Captain America thing by holding down the chopper with his bare hand and then finally go 2 on 1 in the final showdown and i presume that Brixton stays alive and teams up with the Rock in the sequel to this fucked up generic sequel!!

In the trailer, Hobbs ejects Shaw out of the plane... And says to his sister on the in plane screen he has been wanting to do that for so long etc... But that that aspect itself does not appear in the film, nor could it as she was captured during this timeframe. Did they rewrite the film after the trailer was released?  3.  Hobbs brother gives him a hug in the trailer when he returns home... In the film he punches him and has hostility for most of the film.. I do not recall they hug at all.   Miscellaneous : the scene in which hobbs and shaw are about to enter the doors... Rather than shaw opening the door to find multiple badguys, he sees this through a scanner. text: I see alot of people saying that where is the old F&F, is not about cars anymore and all of that. Well, i miss that era too, for some, the majority was for cool cars, speed, and anything illegal. But what the story was about is not really cars, it was about friendship, family, honor, and the etarnal fight between good and bad in movies. It was also about the man and the machine(the car) The passion for it and how a car should represent you, is not about the coolest car in the park, is about to represent you. So yeah, cars died! In case you didn't see it, people no lenger put their hands fixing their cars, tunning them, even Make them. Today cars are made by robots, we barely know how to open the hood of that car, and fixed them in special shops. People got bored of cool cars. The real F&F died people. The story has ended. But since the name of it makes alot of $$ they keep resaleing big names action and stuff like that. These are the "big" movies, how they call them, seeling a story you;ll never live, presenting things you'll never have, fighting things that don't exist. They are cool movies, don't get me wrong, i like to see how far the imagination goes. but, these movies have no story behind, no feeling if i could say... Is just like a very long comercial...
